{
  "stem": "10353.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And being in a factory that made those cases, there was a lot of lumber.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so the lumber was piled up real high in the whole-- in the backyard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And for [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] shelter, for air-raid shelters, they dug trenches underneath those piles of lumber.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And whenever there was a-- the sirens were go on, we would have to run into those trenches to hide.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that particular Sunday morning-- and I believe it was very close to Rosh Hashanah, or maybe the day before Rosh Hashanah-- we received a bombardment from 8:30 in the morning till 2:30 in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And at one point, there was one bomb that fell about 20 meters from us and it created a tremendous crater.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We thought that we were all dead, but luckily, we were safe.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Allied bombs, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, the bombing was so heavy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Budapest got it really strong because the Americans would-- would bomb during the day, and the British would bomb during the night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This was OK.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was the way life was going on until September the 15th.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And on September the 15, the Hungarian government tried to capitulate.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And on a Sunday, the vice-- the regent, Horty-- H-O-R-T-Y-- made an announcement that the Hungarians are suing for peace, or to surrender.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, by that time, of course, they were occupied by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in no time, the Germans swooped down all over.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They arrested the regent and everybody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the Arrow Cross people took over the government.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And all hell broke loose at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because on Monday morning, I ventured out because my commanding officer gave me a false document saying-- which was in the form of a book, which every military personnel had to have.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It-- with a picture on it, with everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It said that I'm Greek Catholic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I ventured out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I ventured out with-- from our compound, and I went to see my boss for whom I worked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had a [INAUDIBLE], a daughter, an only daughter.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I tried to sort of smuggle out the daughter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His daughter.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to their apartment and thought that I can take her to a safe place.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So I had to-- I had to make my way in from the compound into the city.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as I was going in, there were corpses already lying on the streets, covered with newspapers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These Arrow Cross people were going around killing Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because the minute the regent made that announcement by the Hungarians, the Jewish people ventured out of the Jewish-designated houses, which were formed into a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from then on, there was open, blatant physical [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] persecution and killings going on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the Arrow Cross.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They rounded up-- wherever they could find a Jew, they rounded them up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the meantime, for some reason or another, there is-- there are several bridges over the Danube.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One of the bridge, the Saint Margaret Bridge, was bombed and it was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they put up a temporary bridge on pontoons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they rounded up the Jews every day, and they-- these Arrow Cross.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would take them to these pontoons at night, shoot them, and-- into the Danube-- kill them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As for myself, my commanding officer, about six to eight days later, after the Arrow Cross took over, they arrested him as being a friend of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was left alone in the apartment, because we had requisitioned an apartment for him, being as a commanding officer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And also, the office of the brigade was there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was left alone there, and I didn't know what to do, where to go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when they arrested him, they burst in-- the Germans and the Arrow Cross-- with machine guns.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I-- we were on the second floor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I heard them coming, so I sort of dived under a couch in one of the bedrooms.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was hiding there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they came in, and whoever they found there in-- in that apartment, including the commanding officer, they took away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was left alone there with one other fellow that was-- that was also hiding.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
